==English==
===Noun===
'''periodical'''   
 
# A [[publication]] [[issued]] [[regularly]], but less [[frequently]] than [[daily]]
#: a periodical magazine: a magazine or journal published at regular intervals, especially weekly, monthly, or quarterly
# A publication that appears at fixed intervals
# Often contains the most current information in the field, on every conceivable topic, often in greater detail than other publication formats.
# The primary means for communication of original scholarship or creative work at the cutting edge of research in almost all fields.
 



SYNONYM: the term ''serial'' is applied to materials "in any medium issued under the same title in a succession of discrete parts, usually numbered (or dated) and appearing at regular or irregular intervals with no predetermined conclusion."

